Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist
Do not click on unknown or suspicious links
Never share your OTP, passwords, or bank details with anyone
Always check the website URL before entering personal information
Use strong passwords with a mix of letters, numbers, and symbols
Enable two-factor authentication on important accounts
Avoid using public Wi-Fi for online payments or banking
Verify messages and emails before trusting them
Use only official apps and websites for transactions
For reporting cybercrime:
National Cyber Crime Portal: cybercrime.gov.in
Helpline Number: 1930
